—ЩWarchive/external_nushell_repo_backup/nushell.github.io/commands/docs/str_starts-with.mdЩ@2634a05197d3233e254827313b3500b0390e08f9c4c021b0852bb305ef8bddae¶title: str starts-with‘ЁExamplesЪюChecks if input string starts with 'my'.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> 'my_library.rb' | str starts-with 'my'
true

```
Checks if input string starts with 'Car'.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> 'Cargo.toml' | str starts-with 'Car'
true

```
Checks if input string starts with '.toml'.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> 'Cargo.toml' | str starts-with '.toml'
false

```
Checks if input string starts with 'cargo', case-insensitive.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> 'Cargo.toml' | str starts-with --ignore-case 'cargo'
true

```
’ђђЪ4Title: title: str starts-with
Path: Examples
Content:
Checks if input string starts with 'my'.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> 'my_library.rb' | str starts-with 'my'
true

```
Checks if input string starts with 'Car'.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> 'Cargo.toml' | str starts-with 'Car'
true

```
Checks if input string starts with '.toml'.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> 'Cargo.toml' | str starts-with '.toml'
false

```
Checks if input string starts with 'cargo', case-insensitive.
```Fenced(Borrowed("nu"))
> 'Cargo.toml' | str starts-with --ignore-case 'cargo'
true

```
